<TITLE> Harris Chowdhury to spend 10 years behind bars </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 04 (bdnews24.com) - A Dhaka court Sunday sentenced former prime minister Khaleda Zia's political secretary Harris Chowdhury to 59 years in jail and fined him Tk 21 lakh on five counts of charges, including abuse of power and government-transport mishandling. Senior special judge for Dhaka Azizul Haque delivered the verdict in the absence of Harris. According to the sentencing, Harris, who is on the run, was convicted of criminal breach of trust under the Penal Code and criminal misconduct under the Prevention of Corruption Act. In line with the longest-running jail term of all, Harris will have to serve as many as 10 years in jail, as the judge said the jail terms would run concurrently. On the first count of charge, Harris will have to serve six years in jail and pay a fine of Tk 1.6 lakh Public prosecutor Ehsanul Haque Samaji told bdnews24.com that the High Court had stayed the trial of another accused, Amin Badal, brother-in-law of Harris, following his appeal. Sub-inspector Sahabul Islam of Kafrul Police Station filed the case against Harris and Badal on March 25. Anticorruption Commission assistant director Monayem Hossain submitted chargesheet to the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court, Dhaka accusing the two. A Dhaka court earlier sentenced the BNP leader to three years in jail for illegally possessing foreign currency. bdnew
